						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1287, Krōdhi, Bhādrapada, ba. 6, Maṅ[gaḷavāra]</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1364 September 17 Tuesday</hi> (Nija-Bhādrapada), in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Vīra-Bukkaṇṇa-Voḍeya.</hi> It records that, under the orders of the king, <hi rend="bold">Mādarasa</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Maṅgalūru</hi> made a gift of the village <hi rend="bold">Pudu grāma,</hi> to certain Brāhmans (named) free of all taxes. The Brāhmans were to give 12 <hi rend="italic">mūḍes</hi> of rice for the service of the god <hi rend="bold">Mañjināthadēva.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
